1.title: Ruby's Comet Adventure/Rusty's Messy Mishap
1.plot: Ruby wants to see a comet fly by, and Rusty will do everything in his power to make sure his friend's wish comes true!Rusty and Ruby race to fix a leaking underwater oil pipeline before it pollutes the lake and makes it uninhabitable.

2.title: Rusty's Mobile Rivet Lab
2.plot: When Ranger Anna crash lands her planes in the distant savannah, Rusty and Ruby realize they need a new vehicle that can not only travel the distance, but aid them in their builds. Thus, the Mobile Rivet Lab is born!

3.title: Rusty's Piggy Bank Heist/Rusty's Whale of a Problem
3.plot: Rusty forgets the code to his robotic piggy bank, activating its self-defense mode and turning it into a runaway robotic boar. Rusty and Ruby must save a baby whale that's been beached during a storm and reunite it with her family.

4.title: Rusty's Monkey Business/Rusty's Snow Problem
4.plot: When Ranger Anna gets stuck in a tree while observing monkeys, Rusty and Ruby make a monkey of their own to save her... Botarilla!

5.title: Frankie's Botasaur/Rusty's Mega Stacker
5.plot: New neighbor Frankie Fritz bot-naps Botasaur, making Rusty and Ruby go on a chase to get their friend back. Rusty builds a machine that makes and stacks sand blocks, to help Liam build a giant sand castle. But when Bytes bumps into it and causes it to fritz, it runs off and starts making sand structures all over town, trapping people, blocking train tracks, and creating a giant sand castle pyramid in the middle of town.

6.title: Rusty and the Fix It 500/Ice Ice Rusty
6.plot: Frankie Fritz challenges Rusty and Ruby to a multi-stage, all-terrain race around Sparkton Hills, with the Mobile Rivet Lab as the stakes. Rusty and Ruby try to save the school's art fair from being frozen over by Frankie Fritz and his modified Skunk-bot, Frankford.

7.title: Rusty vs. the Robo-Squirrel/Rusty's Day of the Drones
7.plot: When the robotic squirrel Rusty made to keep Bytes occupied goes rogue - swiping all the nuts and bolts from things all over town and causing things to fall apart, Rusty and Ruby must find a way to capture Robo-Squirrel and retrieve his ill gotten loot before the whole town falls apart. Frankie Fritz uses a handful of homemade drones to swipe Rusty and Ruby's Mega Battery, so he can power a giant drone and use it to swipe the entire Rivet Lab!

8.title: Rusty and the Pirates of Sparkton Hills/Rusty and the Mouse Problem
8.plot: Rusty and Ruby set off on their pirate ship in a hunt for a buried treasure. But when Frankie catches wind of what the treasure is, he sets out on a pirate ship of his own to find it first.

9.title: Rusty and the Birthday Surprise/Rusty's Ninja Fish Rescue
9.plot: Rusty and Liam are planning a surprise birthday party at the beach for Ruby, with her favorite ice cream cake, and all her friends from SparktonHills. Mr. Higgins accidentally knocks the power out all over town.

10.title: Rusty's Relaxing Recliner/Rusty and the Stinky Situation
10.plot: Rusty builds his Mom the ultimate relaxing chair, but whenever it hears any noise, it runs away and raises higher into the sky, leaving Rusty's Mom in a precarious position.

11.title: Rusty's Runaway Sled/Rusty's Sky Pie Delivery
11.plot: Bytes and some of the Bits accidentally go on a wild ride in a runaway sled! Rusty, Ruby, and Jack try to find a way to stop the wayward sled. Rusty and Ruby make Officer Carl a giant blueberry pie but struggle to transport the oversized dessert to him in time for lunch.

12.title: Rusty's Show Must Go On/Rusty and the Smore Snatcher
12.plot:

13.title: Rusty's Sick Fix/Rusty's Journey to the Center of Sparkton Hills"
13.plot: The bots catch a virus, wreaking havoc with their aggressive sneezes. The kids must find a cure to stop the mess! Bytes accidentally tunnels his way into a long-forgotten mine - it's up to Rusty, Ruby, and Botasaur to find him

14.title: Rusty's Walk on the Small Side/Liam Gets Birdnapped
14.plot: When Rusty and Ruby accidentally shrink down with Rusty's latest invention, they must fight their way across the Yard to size themselves back up.Liam tells the kids he was "adopted" by a giant mama bird. Now Rusty and Ruby must find a way to rescue him from the protective bird!

15.title: Super Rusty vs. Super Villain Bot/Rusty in Space
15.plot: Wanting to be a hero like Rusty, Frankie creates a Super Villian Bot and programs it to make him look like a hero too. When aliens crash on Earth, Rusty and Ruby must help them get back home in time for the most important alien holiday of the year!

17.title: Rusty and the Heroic Helpers; Rusty's Monkey Rescue
17.plot: Liam and new friend Emily try to emulate their heroes, Rusty and Ruby, only to end up making things worse.

20.plot: When Liam gets trapped inside an ancient elephant temple, Rusty and Ruby enlist the bots to breach the temple and find him. Ultimately, they undertake the recue with a new creature, Elephantbot!

1.title: Rusty's Rex Rescue/Rusty's Park N' Fly
1.plot: In "Rusty's Rex Rescue", Botasaur saves a young boy who finds himself trapped on top of a junk heap. In "Rusty's Park N' Fly", Crush becomes a daredevil rescue pilot to bring an out-of-control RC plane down safely.

2.title: Rusty Digs In/Rusty's Brave Cave Save
2.plot: When Mr. Higgins' award goes missing, it's up to the Rusty, Ruby and Botasaur to find it in time for the ceremony. Sammy gets stuck in a cave, and Rusty gets a big idea from a small creature on how to save him.

3.title: Rusty Dives In/Rusty's Big Top Trouble
3.plot: In "Rusty Dives In", Rusty and the robots must travel underwater to retrieve Ruby's lost tablet. In "Rusty's Big Top Trouble", the team helps repair a circus train before a big show.

4.title: Rusty Marks the Spot/Rusty's Bits on the Fritz
4.plot: When Rusty finds an old pirate's map, he and the gang dig up a lot more than treasure. When the Bits wander into Rusty's parts replicator, the gang winds up with more bits than they bargained for.

5.title: Rusty's Bit in the Woods/Rusty's Stuffy Toughy
5.plot: When Crush wanders off and gets lost, Rusty invents a night flyer to find him in the dark. When Liam loses his stuffy out the train window, Rusty goes on a retrieval mission using a mechanical spider suit to climb up under the trestle and drop down like a spider to get it.

6.title: Rusty Goes Bananas/Rusty's Night Lights
6.plot: When the mischevious monkeys escape from their Animal Park enclosure, Rusty must find a way to lead them back. When the town's power goes out after Ruby takes Crush up for a fun plane flight, there's no light!

7.title: Rusty's Ski Trip Blip/Rusty and the Camp Bandit
7.plot: In "Rusty's Ski Trip Blip", Rusty and the team's ski trip is thwarted by a pile of rocks. In "Rusty and the Camp Bandit", Rusty and Ruby earn their camping badges by saving a trapped opossum.

8.title: Rusty Rocks/Rusty's Balloon Blast
8.plot: In "Rusty Rocks", Rusty and the Bits help Ruby overcome her stage fright. In "Rusty's Balloon Blast", Whirly must save the day when Botasaur inadvertently lets a hot-air balloon fly away with a boy inside.

9.title: Rusty's Nest Friend Forever/Rusty's Flingbot
9.plot: When a rare bird builds his nest in a dangerous location and can't be persuaded to move, Rusty and the gang rebuild his habitat. Rusty and Ruby build a cupcake flinging machine that goes out of control.

10.title: Rusty's Penguin Problem/Rusty's Sand Castle Hassle
10.plot: Rusty and the gang must get some penguins to the Nature Park on the hottest day of the year.

11.title: Rusty's Space Bit/Rusty and the Sneezing Fish
11.plot: When the Bits find a satellite crashed in the scrapyard, Rusty has to find a way to get the satellite bit back home to space! Rusty and the gang must move a sick fish to the Nature Park for treatment.

12.title: Rusty's Water Works/Rusty's Rubbish Race
12.plot: When Rusty accidentally fills a giant beach ball with water instead of air, it's up to the gang to get it to the lake without popping so it doesn't flood the town.

13.title: Rusty in Liam Land/Rusty the Vacuum Kid
13.plot: Liam wants to visit an amusement park but when obstacles delay them, Rusty makes Liam his own theme park. Rusty builds a big vacuum to clean up Liam's mess but the megavac starts to suck up too much!

14.title: Rusty and Captain Scoops/Rusty's Creature Catcher
14.plot: Rusty and Ruby turn Sammy Scoops into Captain Scoops, an ice cream superhero, in order to sell the most ice cream. The kids find the courage to search for a mysterious mythical creature.

15.title: Rusty Learns to Skate/Rusty's Rustic Adventure
15.plot: Rusty builds rocket skates instead of learning how to skate in 'Rusty Learns to Skate', then in 'Rusty's Rustic Adventure', Liam's toy goes missing in the woods, and Rusty and Ruby join the hunt.

16.title: Rusty's Mechanical Animal/Rusty's Spaceship
16.plot: Rusty and Ruby make Ranger Anna a robotic pet in 'Rusty's Mechanical Animal', then in 'Rusty's Spaceship', Rusty builds Liam a spaceship which wreaks havoc on the town.

17.title: Rusty and the Bit Police/Rusty's Jam at the Dam
17.plot: On a busy day, Officer Carl needs to be in too many places at the same time. On a nature trip, Rusty, Ruby, and Anna discover that a local beaver hasn't been able to repair its dam due to a sore tooth.

18.title: Rusty's BotaFort/Rusty's Bull Dozer
18.plot: When Rusty, Ruby, and Liam build a fort that Botasaur can't fit into, he runs away to make his own fort. Rusty and Ruby help Mr. Higgins fix his broken bulldozer, only to have it cause mayhem all over town.

19.title: Rusty's Alien Invasion/Rusty's Running Car
19.plot: When the comic book action figures Rusty created for Liam come alive, they behave just like their conquering characters.Sammy and Rusty must get back to town before the yummy flower they picked for Sammy's sorbet turns yucky.

20.title: Rusty Feels Peachy/Rusty's Monkey Mayhem
20.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

21.title: Rusty's Pet Project/Rusty Gets Stuck
21.plot: When Botasaur gets tired from playing, Rusty builds him a bigger battery - but with it comes more energy! Ruby demonstrates her newest invention - the world's strongest glue - and gets all of Sparkton Hills stuck.

22.title: Rusty's Mysterious Mystery/Rusty's Yard-Cade Game
22.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

23.title: Rusty's Spooky Adventure/Rusty Loses the Bits
23.plot: Rusty and Liam love it when Mr. Higgins makes Sparkton Hills seem haunted with his "Spooky Adventure". Tthe Bits escape from the Recycling Yard, Rusty and Ruby read Whirly's clues to find out where they went.

24.title: Rusty's Dancing Suit/Rusty Bee Good
24.plot: Mr. Higgins wants to go to the town dance, but thinks he's a terrible dancer. So Rusty and Ruby build a suit that dances for him... with unexpected results.Rusty accidentally causes bees to abandon their hive in the Recycling Yard and must lure them back home before they cause problems in town.

25.title: Rusty's Plant Predicament/Rusty's Beach Day Delay
25.plot: Super stinky weeds invade town... but Botasaur thinks they're delicious! Rusty turns Botasaur into an all-terrain vehicle, so his robotic buddy can track all the stinkweeds down and eat them before they spread even more. Rusty turns Botasaur into the ultimate beach day gadget, but Rusty can't get to the beach to play with him because they keep stopping to help friends in need.

26.title: Rusty's Kitty Catastrophe/Robo Rusty
26.plot: Rusty builds a robot version of himself, so he can do two things at once. But when Robo-Rusty gets carried away and builds a giant robot out of playground equipment, Rusty must save the day.Rusty and Ruby build a robotic buddy for Botasaur, a Kittybot! But when Botasaur accidentally scares her away, Rusty and Ruby must track her down to reconcile their two giant robotic pets.

plot: An engineer named Rusty leads a team of rescue robots. Together, they invent their way out of difficult situations.
